Nov 25 2009 	Great location blah rooms wearing down. Slightly musty.	This was a tremendously underwhelming hotel. I don't consider myself a hotel snob at all - I stay in budget motels regularly and don't mind. But this hotel, especially for the location (right in the middle of Market St. in downtown San Fran at the turn-around point for the cable car), was just exceedingly blah. The room was small and ugly, the shower head was eye-level, there was chipping/cracked paint, the &quot;closet&quot; was laughably-small, there was a stain on our duvet (or whatever you call that thing at the foot of the bed that isn't actually a blanket), and when we asked for more blankets the ones they brought were frayed and torn (though admittedly clean). The whole thing felt old, and not in the charming way, but more in the &quot;shouldn't they fix that?&quot; way.The bathroom wasn't especially clean when we got there either (soap scum in the soap dishes). There was also some sort of plastic mattress pad on the bed that creaked every time my wife or I moved. This was very annoying and made it one of the least-comfortable hotel beds I've slept in. There was no air conditioning or heat in our room (some rooms apparently have a steam-heater, whatever that means), though thankfully they brought up a space heater on our request. Service was fine and prompt, though not overly friendly - perhaps they were just very busy. Lots of great food, shopping, and attractions around. The location truly is fantastic, and honestly if you're looking to be right in the heart of San Fran it's one of the best options. Doing some shopping around on the various travel sites we ended up getting this for about $100 a night, which was a bargain for where it was, even with the dingy rooms. I would have been annoyed had I paid $150+, but perhaps that's because I'm used to cheap hotels in non-touristy locations. If you want a great location and are not planning on spending much time in the room then this will certainly fulfill your needs. If on the other hand you'll be in the room a lot (my wife had to study so we were holed up for quite a while) I might recommend finding another option.	
