Jun 15 2008 	Perfect medium-class SF hotel	I was in SF for a convention and wanted to stay a few extra days on my own expense - so I shifted from the expensive Hotel480 to Powell, and what an improvement in how I was treated! The staff is certainly the most helpful I have ever experienced. The hotel is medium/budget priced, so don't expect fancy amenities like minibar or breakfast restaurant (but who cares, Lori's Diner and a hundred other restaurants are in walking distance!), but the location is absolutely perfect, the treatment is kind and professional, and the rooms are tidy and quite charming. Also free wireless internet - something the snobby Hotel480 charged an additional $10/day for! Your only alternatives for a decent hotel with excellent location are the Hilton, Westin, and other $250+ hotels - so the decision is up to your wallet!	
Jun 10 2008 	Nice hotel PERFECT location	I stayed here with my wife on an anniversary trip to San Francisco, the first time to the city for both of us, and we couldn't have stayed at a better place! The location is mentioned by just about all of the reviews, and I couldn't agree more that it is perfect. The cable car turnaround is literally right out the fron door, and Market St. is about 50 steps away, on which there is a plethora of public transportation lines. We especially loved the F line, which is served by ~20 historic street cars from around the world. It runs from the Castro, down Market St to the Embarcadero and right to Fisherman's Wharf. This is a great way to get from the hotel to the Alcatraz tour. Overall, a car is definitely not necessary since you can take the BART from SFO, walk from the BART station to the hotel, and then be so close to all the transportation you can ever imagine needing.The hotel itself was clean, friendly, and comfortable. There is no A/C, but this seems to be standard in SF given the mild temps. We were there in early June and we never needed the A/C. The hotel seems to be recently renovated, which was nice, but our bathroom was circa 1950. It was clean and functional, but just not up to the standard of many hotels these days. I did notice the &quot;old&quot; smell that some have mentioned but it is not unpleasant and you soon don't even notice it.The staff is friendly and helpful, although they kinda struck out when it came to local dining recommendations.Overall, this is a great place for anyone visiting the city who wants to really get around and see things.	
