Mar 11 2008 	Nice little hotel with fantastic location.	My girlfriend found this hotel online and suggested to book it for a relatively inexpensive long President's Day weekend. Reviews looked good and the location was ideal for public transportation since we were flying in (cheaper than driving from San Diego!) so we booked it.First, it was awesome to come out of the BART station and find the hotel maybe 20 steps away. 10 steps away is the cable car turn around. We were at the hotel at about 9:30am and were relieved to find out that the hotel was able to check us in early (so we could take a well needed nap). Check in was fast and the staff friendly and helpful.We got to the room. It's clear the hotel is fairly old, but the paint in the room and halls is fresh, if a few layers thick from many years service. Carpet appeared to be new. The room was somewhat small, but I didn't feel cramped. I knew there was no A/C, but I couldn't find a heater thermostat. I'm thinking maybe it's old enough to use radiant heat? I was fine but my girlfriend was a bit cold at times.Furniture was fine and the flat screen TV on the desk worked fine and helped maximize space in the room. The bed and linens were clean and comfortable. Bathroom was fairly small but in nice shape. Shower was clean but the water couldn't get hot enough for me. Even at the hottest setting, it was merely warm, which was a disappointment to my weary muscles after walking all over town. Our room was facing into the outdoor center area of the building, which meant the view was crummy, but we were also away from the ringing bells of the cable cars outside which others have complained about. Our room was quiet and we had no interruptions. We had to call the front desk to get a hair drier and one of the staff showed up about 3 minutes later to deliver it.As mentioned before, the location is great, and several MUNI bus and street car lines are within a block of the hotel. Union Square is very close by. I made a reservation for a late Valentine's day dinner at a restaurant based on reviews online and it even turned out to be just a block from the hotel. We were able to walk to Chinatown easily.Overall we were very happy with our choice and would gladly stay there again.	
