Feb 20 2007 	Great location very comfortable	My boyfriend and I stayed at the Powell over a long weekend and were very comfortable, thanks to a little effort in advance.It seems that when you book a room at the Powell through hotels.com or another third-party service, you may not be guaranteed the room you thought you were getting. So the day before we checked in, I (who arrived in SF a day early) went in person to the front desk and asked to pre-book a specific room in the renovated section of the hotel, on a high floor, on the back/inside of the building (away from the cablecar stop). The 5 minutes this took gave us a comfortable double room on the top floor -- silent, clean, bright, all new bathroom fixtures -- basically everything you could ask for in a bargain boutique hotel. My advice: at least call a day ahead to make sure the hotel is aware of your room preferences. The staff is very helpful and willing to make these arrangements for you.Otherwise, great location (at the trolley and Muni/Bart, 3 blocks from Union Square, across from the Westview shopping complex with salons, movie theater and grocery store), cute decor, helpful staff. Wonderful deal if you don't insist on the Ritz.	
