Aug 11 2005 	Good location but needs a bit of an update	I stayed at the Powell Hotel Aug 5-10th for a trade show while in San Fran. I chose it based on location and pricing. The front desk was very helpful and friendly, and always went out of their way to assist me. The lobby is nice and newer, with seating and great design. There is a small cafe in the lobby which serves coffee, pastries and the like also. The actual hotel rooms themselves leave a bit to be desired. As soon as you get out of the elevator, the hallways smell quite musty and old. The hotel itself is a landmark in terms of age so I can understand the smell. But the hallway carpets also had water stain marks and were dimly lit. Not a great first impression. The rooms are basic and also have a damp, old musty smell. The room faced inwards, looking across at other rooms, which was a bit of a letdown, since the interior corridor is a bit drab to look at and makes the room a bit darker. Not to mention the fact that you have a LOT of other rooms looking in on you. It didn't really even cut out the noise from the streets, so I would have rather been facing the street. You can definitely hear noise from the cable cars and crowds, but it wasn't unbearable. Lots of pigeons too!The bathrooms were nice and bright white, the towels crisp and clean. However, they have done something with the tap so that the hot water is limited, which led to some lukewarm showers and the like. The fan in the bathroom definitely needed cleaning. They have a nice iron and board in the room, but no plugs except over by the desk!! Small things and rather inconsequential for a budget traveller who might just need a cheaper place to lay their head at night, but it didn't make coming home after a long day at the trade show much fun or cozy. Don't get me wrong, I am not a picky traveller. But I think with a few improvements this hotel could be a LOT better. I did end up hearing that some rooms were refurbished so try to get those. The staff is really very nice and that prevented me from making any major complaints, also since I was working most of the time and never in the room. If you want a cheap, safe place to stay, it's fine. If you want a bit more comfort or coziness, spend a tiny bit more and do that.	
