May 16 2005	Great value friendly service	My husband and I seek out smaller, affordable hotels when we visit big cities. Sometimes we are pleasantly surprised; other times, less pleasantly so. This time, was one of the pleasant ones. This is an older, small hotel. The location is as fabulous as advertised: right at the Powell street cable car turn around, just steps from the Powell Street BART/Muni station. I cannot imagine any better location if you want/need to stay in downtown San Francisco, especially given the price we paid (about $100 per night, including tax). The only downside to the location is that it can be a little noisy, but that didn't really bother us. The lobby and public areas in the hotel have been updated more recently than the room we stayed in, but our room was acceptable in terms of size, repair, and cleanliness. The elevators are older and a little slow, but there are only 6 floors, so you can always take the stairs if you don't want to wait. The front desk staff were very friendly and professional. We only stayed/paid for one night, but they held our luggage for us most of a second day after we checked out because the Amtrak bus we were to catch did not leave until 9 pm. This hotel is literally across the street from the San Francisco Shopping Center Amtrak bus stop, by the way, which made it absolutely perfect for us. We got to maximize our sight-seeing time with a minimum of expense and fuss, and a minimum of walking to the bus stop with our baggage when it was time to leave. Overall, this hotel is a great value. It's secure, reasonably maintained, and very reasonably priced for the location and service you get. I plan to stay here again the next time I visit San Francisco.	
